  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Facilities Engineer (Data Center)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Good understanding of M&amp;E infrastructure.</li>\n  <li>Supervise preventive maintenance activities and ad-hoc works orders on mechanical, electrical and other installed M&amp;E systems and ensure timely and quality work.</li>\n  <li>Experience working in critical M&amp;E facilities or experience in ACMV, electrical or fire systems will be an advantage.</li>\n  <li>Able to carry out impact assessment during system fault and technically sound to contain fault to ensure M&amp;E system service continuity.</li>\n  <li>Ensure proper escalation in accordance to incident escalation process.</li>\n  <li>Carry out work in accordance to site processes and requirements.</li>\n  <li>Proactively look out for site abnormalities and possible areas of improvement, recommend solutions and put up proposal to Engineer (Lead).</li>\n  <li>Able to prepare and review SOPs, MOPs and EOPs.</li>\n  <li>General facilities duties, including monitoring of equipment and report on daily condition.</li>\n  <li>Occasionally perform simple repair work such as lamp replacement or door repair.</li>\n  <li>Any other duties assigned by Engineer (Lead).</li>\n  <li>Flexible with 24x7 rotating shifts.</li>\n</ul>",
